The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Thursday, July 01, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 East Bengal have signed defender Louis Aniweta from Haywards Sporing in the IFA inter-club transfers on Wednesday. Aniweta had earlier taken the inter-state clearance to play for the red-and-gold shirts for 2004-05 season. 				 																																																	In another move, Ever-Ready Association gained Manoj Joshi on this day. 				 																																																	In an interesting development former international goalkeeper Shibaji Banerjee has appealed to the IFA to cancel all the CFL matches scheduled on Monday because of Euro Cup final in the late hours of Sunday. He felt junior footballers need to be able to watch this match.				 																																																	 The West Bengal Badminton Association (WBBA) will hold a 14-day advance coaching camp for the junior players at the indoor badminton hall at SAI here. 				 																																																	The camp will begin on Thursday. Former Thomas Cupper and Indian international Dipu Ghosh will inaugurate the camp. 				 																																																	 The West Bengal Kayaking and Canoeing Association will hold a training session for various age-groups at the Nalban boating complex shortly. The training session will be inaugurated on Sunday. There will also be live demonstrations of the sport. 				 																																																	FOOTBALL: CFL Super Division matches  Ever-Ready Association vs George Telegraph (Barasat Stadium); Peerless vs CFC (Mohammedan Sporting); Eastern Railway vs FCI (East Bengal); CPT vs Railway FC (Mohun Bagan); Mohammedan AC vs Wari AC (Howrah Stadium). Matches from 3.30 pm.
